{"id":722,"date":"2022-04-11T16:28:00","date_gmt":"2022-04-11T13:28:00","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/?p=722"},"modified":"2022-03-23T21:54:11","modified_gmt":"2022-03-23T19:54:11","slug":"making-international-and-domestic-payments","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/making-international-and-domestic-payments\/","title":{"rendered":"How to make international and domestic payments using Digital Payment methods"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p>Digital payment methods refer to a form of paperless, cashless, and contactless payment methods. Tech advancements have made it easier for the world to embrace payment methods that use machine learning\/AI and smartphone apps.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>In the past two years, the fear of germs, global lockdowns, and the ease of online shopping has helped increase the adoption of banking as a service platform. Gen Z, for example, has quickly <a href=\"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/domestic-vs-international-payments-differences\/#:~:text=Today%2C%20digital-,payments,-have%20made%20it\">embraced online payment<\/a> methods such as:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>\u2022 Buy now, pay later (BNPL)<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>\u2022 Electronic wallet services<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>\u2022 Peer-to-peer payment apps<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>\u2022 Contactless payments<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>As competition in this sector continues to intensify, the addition of value-added services can assist payment processors in differentiating themselves from their competition. They also have an opportunity to begin generating revenue from the diversification of services.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div id=\"ez-toc-container\" class=\"ez-toc-v2_0_45 counter-hierarchy ez-toc-counter ez-toc-grey ez-toc-container-direction\">\n<div class=\"ez-toc-title-container\">\n<p class=\"ez-toc-title\">Table of Contents<\/p>\n<span class=\"ez-toc-title-toggle\"><a href=\"#\" class=\"ez-toc-pull-right ez-toc-btn ez-toc-btn-xs ez-toc-btn-default ez-toc-toggle\" area-label=\"ez-toc-toggle-icon-1\"><label for=\"it